    "While the pandemic was framed as a contributing factor to burnout, surgeons also emphasized that the patient-related pressures being experienced from COVID-19 were largely a result of pre-existing issues in the healthcare system being exacerbated.",
    "The increasing expectations of patients and referring physicians were noted as contributors to the pressures faced by surgeons in their careers.",
    "One participant stated: \"So it [patient-care related pressures] definitely existed pre-pandemic, but everything has been worsened because wait times are so much worse than they used to be."
